procedures.name: Venipuncture

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood for laboratory studies including hematology, blood chemistry, pregnancy tests, hormone levels, and pharmacokinetics.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full physical examination including an examination of all major body systems and breasts, height (at screening only), and weight.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Assessment
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Measurement of blood pressure and pulse rate.

procedures.name: 12-Lead Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: 12-Lead ECG
procedures.description: A 12-lead ECG performed in triplicate to assess cardiac function.

procedures.name: Computed Tomography Scan

code.decode: Computed tomography, abdomen and pelvis; without contrast material

procedures.label: CT Scan
procedures.description: CT scans of the chest, abdomen, pelvis, and any other clinically indicated sites of disease for tumor assessment.

procedures.name: Magnetic Resonance Imaging

code.decode: Magnetic resonance (eg, proton) imaging, abdomen; without contrast material(s), followed by contrast material(s) and further sequences

procedures.label: MRI
procedures.description: MRI scans of the chest, abdomen, pelvis, and any other clinically indicated sites of disease for tumor assessment.

procedures.name: Radionuclide Bone Scan

code.decode: Bone and/or joint imaging; whole body

procedures.label: Bone Scan
procedures.description: Whole body radionuclide bone scan to assess for bone lesions.

procedures.name: Ophthalmic Examination
procedures.label: Eye Exam
procedures.description: Ophthalmic examination by an ophthalmologist, including lens opacity grading.

procedures.name: Hematology Testing
procedures.label: Hematology Panel
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis of blood samples for hemoglobin, WBC, absolute neutrophil count, and platelet count.

procedures.name: Blood Chemistry Testing
procedures.label: Chemistry Panel
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis of blood samples for AST/ALT, alkaline phosphatase, sodium, potassium, magnesium, total calcium, total bilirubin, BUN, serum creatinine, and albumin.

procedures.name: Hemoglobin A1c Test
procedures.label: HbA1c Test
procedures.description: Prospective monitoring of hemoglobin A1c to characterize whether or not palbociclib affects glucose metabolism.

procedures.name: Pharmacokinetic Sampling
procedures.label: PK Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of plasma PK samples to assess drug concentrations of palbociclib and fulvestrant.

procedures.name: Tumor Assessment
procedures.label: Tumor Assessment
procedures.description: Evaluation of tumor response using imaging studies (CT, MRI, Bone Scan) and clinical evaluation, initially guided by RECIST version 1.1.

procedures.name: ECOG Performance Status
procedures.label: ECOG PS
procedures.description: Assessment of patient's level of functioning in terms of their ability to care for themselves, daily activity, and physical ability.

procedures.name: Survival Follow-up
procedures.label: Survival Follow-up
procedures.description: Follow-up visits or telephone contact conducted every 3 months to assess survival status.

medicalDevices.name: Computed Tomography Scanner
medicalDevices.label: CT Scanner
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform CT scans of the chest, abdomen, and pelvis for tumor assessment.

medicalDevices.name: Magnetic Resonance Imaging Scanner
medicalDevices.label: MRI Scanner
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform MRI scans of the chest, abdomen, and pelvis for tumor assessment.

medicalDevices.name: Radionuclide Bone Scanner
medicalDevices.label: Bone Scanner
medicalDevices.description: Device used for whole body radionuclide bone scans.
